With the Covid-19 pandemic, there are so many new things we need to grow accustomed to.
It’s okay if you’re unsure of the difference between a respirator and a ventilator, or the distinction between isolation and quarantine.
(It’s short for “severe acute respiratory syndrome coronavirus 2.”)Covid-19 — The disease caused by the virus SARS-CoV-2.
The World Health Organization declared Covid-19 a pandemic on March 11, 2020.
An epidemic is a less severe designation than a pandemic, but there is an overlap between the two terms.